1️⃣ express.json() என்றால் என்ன?

Tamil Explanation:
express.json() என்பது client இருந்து வரும் JSON data-ஐ read பண்ண Express-க்கு உதவும் middleware.

Frontend JSON data அனுப்பும் போது அதை JavaScript object ஆக convert பண்ணி req.body-ல வைக்கிறது.

Interview Sentence (English):
👉 “express.json() is a built-in middleware used to parse incoming JSON requests and make the data available in req.body.”

2️⃣ Why we use app.use(express.json())?

Frontend (React / Postman) usually JSON format-ல data send பண்ணும்.

Example request:

{
  "name": "Gowtham",
  "email": "gowtham@gmail.com"
}

இந்த data-ஐ backend read பண்ண express.json() தேவை.

3️⃣ Without express.json()

Backend:

import express from "express"

const app = express()

app.post("/register",(req,res)=>{
 console.log(req.body)
})

Output:

undefined

ஏன்னா Express JSON data read பண்ண முடியாது.

4️⃣ With express.json()
import express from "express"

const app = express()

app.use(express.json())

app.post("/register",(req,res)=>{
 console.log(req.body)
})

Request:

{
 "name":"Gowtham"
}

Output:

{ name: 'Gowtham' }
5️⃣ How it works (Flow)

Flow diagram:

Client Request (JSON)
        ↓
express.json() middleware
        ↓
JSON → JavaScript Object convert
        ↓
req.body
        ↓
Route handler
6️⃣ Real MERN example

Frontend (React):

axios.post("http://localhost:5000/register",{
 name:"Gowtham",
 email:"gowtham@gmail.com"
})

Backend (Express):

app.use(express.json())

app.post("/register",(req,res)=>{
 const {name,email} = req.body
 console.log(name,email)
})

Output:

Gowtham gowtham@gmail.com
7️⃣ Why app.use()?
app.use(express.json())

Meaning:

👉 Express app இந்த middleware-ஐ எல்லா request-க்கும் use பண்ணும்.

அதனால் எந்த route இருந்தாலும் JSON read ஆகும்.

8️⃣ express.json() type

Express-ல இது built-in middleware.

Examples:

Middleware	Use
express.json()	JSON request parse
express.urlencoded()	form data parse
cors()	cross origin allow
9️⃣ When it runs?

express.json() run ஆகும்:

✔ POST request
✔ PUT request
✔ PATCH request

அதாவது body data இருக்கும் request-ல.

🔟 Interview Short Answer

👉 “express.json() is a built-in Express middleware that parses incoming JSON requests and makes the parsed data available in req.body for route handlers.”

